For class Iris-virginica, Iris-versicolor and Iris-setosa- it can be seen all are positively correlated. Points which can be noted apart from the points already mentioned before are - 1) For Iris-virginica and Iris-versicolor - 1) Sepal length in cm and Sepal width in cm are positively correlated 2) Sepal width in cm and Petal width in cm are positively correlated 3) Petal length in cm and Sepal width in cm are positively correlated 2) For Iris-versicolor alone - 1) Petal width in cm and Sepal length in cm are positively correlated 3) For Iris-setosa - 1) Sepal length in cm and Sepal width in cm are more positively correlated as compared to others 2) Petal length in cm and Petal width in cm are more positively correlated as compared to others
